    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Workflow 1 – Scheduler\nThis workflow acts as the entry point of AgencyPulseAI. It runs on a predefined schedule, retrieves all active clients from the clients table, and creates a new record in the report_jobs table with a status of PENDING for each client. The workflow initializes the reporting pipeline and ensures that every active client enters the automated report generation process.",
        "height": 560,
        "width": 1888
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -3664,
        -1600
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "id": "d0a1ae4f-f16d-4373-9cb1-d4f1b03e27cc",
      "name": "Sticky Note1"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Workflow 2 – Data Collector\nThis workflow processes all PENDING report jobs by collecting website analytics and search performance data from Google Analytics 4 (GA4) and Google Search Console (GSC). The collected metrics are normalized and stored in the metrics table. Once data collection is completed successfully, the report job status is updated to GENERATING, making it available for AI-based report creation.",
        "height": 768,
        "width": 1888,
        "color": 5
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -3664,
        -896
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "id": "44244a86-f6f3-447b-ba32-5231938e868b",
      "name": "Sticky Note2"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Workflow 3 – AI Generator\nThis workflow generates professional website performance reports using OpenAI. It retrieves all report jobs with a status of GENERATING, fetches the corresponding analytics data from the metrics table, and creates an AI-powered report containing executive summaries, traffic analysis, SEO insights, recommendations, and action plans. The generated report is stored in the reports table, and the job status is updated to EMAILING.",
        "height": 592,
        "width": 1904,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -3664,
        16
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "id": "188dcddd-9cf6-464a-8daf-8bfa639082be",
      "name": "Sticky Note3"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Workflow 4 – Email Sender\nThis workflow is responsible for delivering AI-generated reports to clients. It retrieves report jobs with a status of EMAILING, fetches the generated report and client information, builds an HTML email, and sends the report to the client's registered email address. After successful delivery, the reports table is updated with email_sent = 1, and the report job status is changed to COMPLETED, marking the end of the reporting lifecycle.",
        "height": 560,
        "width": 1696,
        "color": 7
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -1664,
        -1600
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "id": "322eddc8-6f46-45c7-b0ff-364db24e53ed",
      "name": "Sticky Note4"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.splitInBatches",
      "typeVersion": 3,
      "position": [
        -1200,
        -1392
      ],
      "id": "4159a88a-8fd6-4a2b-845e-7720c9d7ef78",
      "name": "Process Email Jobs"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Workflow 5 – Error Monitor\nThis workflow provides centralized error handling and monitoring for AgencyPulseAI. It is triggered whenever any workflow execution fails, captures execution details such as workflow name, failed node, error message, stack trace, and execution ID, and stores the information in the error_logs table. It also sends an alert email to the administrator, enabling rapid troubleshooting and ensuring the reliability of the reporting system.",
        "height": 752,
        "width": 1696,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -1664,
        -880
      ],
